, Scotland":"Leslie, Aberdeenshire, Scotland","Rathes,Moray,Scotland":"Rothes, Moray, Skotsko, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland"},"da":{"about 1071–Abt 1176":"omkring 1071–omkring 1176","1071–1176":"1071–1176","1110–Male":"1110–Afdød","1155–1248":"1155–1248","1157–Male":"1157–Afdød","1040–1121":"1040–1121","1030–1121":"1030–1121","about 1071":"omkring 1071","1121":"1121","1110":"1110","1176":"1176","1030":"1030","1040":"1040","1071":"1071","1248":"1248","1157":"1157","Abt 1176":"omkring 1176","1155":"1155","about 1176":"omkring 1176","EST 1121":"omkring 1121","Leslie, Fifeshire, Scotland":"Leslie, Fife, Skotland, United Kingdom","Leslie, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Leslie, Aberdeenshire, Skotland","Rathes,Moray,Scotland":"Rothes, Moray, Skotland, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Skotland"},"nl":{"about 1071–Abt 1176":"circa 1071–circa 1176","1071–1176":"1071–1176","1110–Male":"1110–Overleden","1155–1248":"1155–1248","1157–Male":"1157–Overleden","1040–1121":"1040–1121","1030–1121":"1030–1121","about 1071":"circa 1071","1121":"1121","1110":"1110","1176":"1176","1030":"1030","1040":"1040","1071":"1071","1248":"1248","1157":"1157","Abt 1176":"circa 1176","1155":"1155","about 1176":"circa 1176","EST 1121":"circa 1121","Leslie, Fifeshire, Scotland":"Leslie, Fife, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Leslie, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Leslie, Aberdeenshire, Schotland","Rathes,Moray,Scotland":"Rothes, Moray, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Scotland":"Schotland"},"en":{"about 1071–Abt 1176":"about 1071–about 1176","1071–1176":"1071–1176","1110–Male":"1110–Deceased","1155–1248":"1155–1248","1157–Male":"1157–Deceased","1040–1121":"1040–1121","1030–1121":"1030–1121","about 1071":"about 1071","1121":"1121","1110":"1110","1176":"1176","1030":"1030","1040":"1040","1071":"1071","1248":"1248","1157":"1157","Abt 1176":"about 1176","1155":"1155","about 1176":"about 1176","EST 1121":"about 1121","Leslie, Fifeshire, Scotland":"Leslie, Fife, Scotland, United Kingdom","Leslie, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Leslie, Aberdeenshire, Scotland","Rathes,Moray,Scotland":"Rothes, Moray, Scotland, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Leslie","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from a barony in Aberdeenshire, which is first recorded <i>c.</i> 1180 in the form <i>Lesslyn</i>, of obscure origin. Leslie in Fife is said to be named for this place; in some cases the surname may come from there.","English: from the Middle English female personal name <i>Lecelin</i>, a double diminutive of <i>Lece</i>. See   Leece   and   Lesley  .","History: The Scottish Clan Leslie claims descent from Bartolf, a Hungarian nobleman who came to Scotland in 1068 or 1070 in the retinue of Queen Margaret. She was an English princess who had been born and brought up in Hungary and who went on to marry King Malcolm III of Scotland. Members of the clan have held several titles in the peerage of Scotland, including Earl of Rothes (from 1437)."],"variants":[{"name":"Leece","meanings":["English: from a medieval female personal name, <i>Lece</i>, a short form of <i>Lettice</i> (from Latin <i>Laetitia</i>, meaning ‘happiness, gaiety’).","English: variant of   Lees  .","Irish: shortened form of Gaelic <i>Mac Giolla Íosa</i>, Manx <i>Mac Guilley Yeesey</i> ‘son of <i>Giolla Íosa</i> (devotee or servant of Jesus)’. Ballaleece (‘Leece's farm’) in Kirk German was the family's main seat."]},{"name":"Lesslie","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Leslie  ."]},{"name":"Lesley","meanings":["Scottish and northern Irish: variant of   Leslie  ."]},{"name":"Laslie","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Leslie  ."]},{"name":"Lessley","meanings":["English (Norfolk): variant of   Leslie  ."]},{"name":"Lasley","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Leslie  ."]}]},{"name":"Malcolm","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Anglicized form of the medieval Gaelic name <i>Mael Coluim</i> ‘devotee of St Columba’. Columba was a 6th-century monk of Irish origin who played a leading part in the conversion to Christianity of Scotland and northern England;  see also  Callum   and   Colm .  He has always been one of the most popular saints in Scotland, but in the Middle Ages it was felt to be presumptuous to give the names of saints directly to children; instead their blessing was invoked by prefixing the name with <i>mael</i> ‘devotee of’ or <i>gille</i> ‘servant of’. Since the 1930s the given name has been used widely in the English-speaking world, not just by those with Scottish connections."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Malcolm Leslie 2nd of Leslie, Lesslyn, Constable of Inverurie was born about 1071, in Rothes, Moray, Scotland, United Kingdom, his father, Bartholomew Leslie Governor of Edinburgh Castle, was 32 and his mother, Beatrix Princess of Scotland, was 42. He had at least 3 sons. He died about 1176, in Leslie, Aberdeenshire, Scotland, at the age of 107."},"et":{"about 1071–Abt 1176":"umbes 1071–umbes 1176","1071–1176":"1071–1176","1110–Male":"1110–Surnud","1155–1248":"1155–1248","1157–Male":"1157–Surnud","1040–1121":"1040–1121","1030–1121":"1030–1121","about 1071":"umbes 1071","1121":"1121","1110":"1110","1176":"1176","1030":"1030","1040":"1040","1071":"1071","1248":"1248","1157":"1157","Abt 1176":"umbes 1176","1155":"1155","about 1176":"umbes 1176","EST 1121":"umbes 1121","Leslie, Fifeshire, Scotland":"Leslie, Fife, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Leslie, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Leslie, Aberdeenshire, Scotland","Rathes,Moray,Scotland":"Rothes, Moray, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fi":{"about 1071–Abt 1176":"noin 1071–noin 1176","1071–1176":"1071–1176","1110–Male":"1110–Kuollut","1155–1248":"1155–1248","1157–Male":"1157–Kuollut","1040–1121":"1040–1121","1030–1121":"1030–1121","about 1071":"noin 1071","1121":"1121","1110":"1110","1176":"1176","1030":"1030","1040":"1